<h2>Dashboard Layout</h2>

<h3>Page 1: Prudential Norms Overview</h3>

<p>This page gives supervisors a single-glance view of all 6 norms across all institutions.</p>

<h4>Top Row &#8212; 6 KPI Cards (one per PNR)</h4>

<p>Each card shows:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Metric name (e.g., &#8220;PNR13: Fixed Assets&#8221;)</li>
  <li>Sector-wide current month average ratio</li>
  <li>Threshold value</li>
  <li>Number of institutions in breach</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Power BI Visual:</b> Card or Multi-row Card<br>
<b>Conditional Formatting:</b> Green if sector average below threshold, Red if above</p>

<h4>Middle Section &#8212; Compliance Heatmap Matrix</h4>

<p>A matrix table where:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Rows</b> = Institutions (Stakeholder_Name)</li>
  <li><b>Columns</b> = PNR13, PNR14, PNR15, PNR16, PNR17, PNR18</li>
  <li><b>Cell Values</b> = Computed ratio (%)</li>
  <li><b>Conditional Formatting (background color):</b></li>
</ul>

<table>
  <tr><th>Status</th><th>Condition</th><th>Background</th></tr>
  <tr class="compliant"><td>Compliant</td><td>Ratio below 70% of threshold</td><td>Green</td></tr>
  <tr class="warning"><td>Warning</td><td>Ratio between 70%&#8211;100% of threshold</td><td>Amber / Yellow</td></tr>
  <tr class="breach"><td>Breach</td><td>Ratio above threshold</td><td>Red</td></tr>
</table>

<p><b>Power BI Visual:</b> Matrix<br>
<b>Slicers:</b> CATEGORY_TYPE, Year_Month</p>

<p>This is the most critical visual &#8212; it lets inspectors immediately spot which institutions are breaching which norms.</p>

<h4>Bottom Row &#8212; Breach Count Bar Chart</h4>

<p>Horizontal bar chart showing the count of institutions in breach per PNR.</p>

<p><b>Power BI Visual:</b> Clustered Bar Chart</p>
<ul>
  <li>X-axis: Count of institutions in breach</li>
  <li>Y-axis: PNR indicator names</li>
  <li>Conditional color: Red bars</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h3>Page 2: Prudential Norms Trends</h3>

<p>This page shows 12-month trends for each norm, allowing supervisors to identify deteriorating institutions before they breach.</p>

<h4>Layout &#8212; 2&#215;3 Grid of Line Charts</h4>

<table>
  <tr><th>Position</th><th>Chart</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Top Left</td><td>PNR13: Investment in Fixed Assets &#8212; threshold line at 50%</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Top Right</td><td>PNR14: Land &amp; Buildings &#8212; threshold line at 5%</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Middle Left</td><td>PNR15: Non-Earning Assets &#8212; threshold line at 10%</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Middle Right</td><td>PNR16: Borrowing Ratio &#8212; threshold line at 25%</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Bottom Left</td><td>PNR17: Placement Limits &#8212; threshold line at 25%</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Bottom Right</td><td>PNR18: Equity Shares &#8212; threshold line at 25%</td></tr>
</table>

<p><b>Each Line Chart Configuration:</b></p>
<ul>
  <li><b>X-axis:</b> Year_Month (12 months rolling)</li>
  <li><b>Y-axis:</b> Ratio (%)</li>
  <li><b>Lines:</b> One line per selected institution (use LE_Book slicer)</li>
  <li><b>Constant Line:</b> Regulatory threshold (red dashed line)</li>
  <li><b>Data Labels:</b> On for latest month only</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Power BI Visual:</b> Line Chart with Constant Line<br>
<b>Slicers (synced across all 6 charts):</b> CATEGORY_TYPE, LE_Book / Stakeholder_Name</p>

<hr>

<h2>Detailed Visual Specifications per PNR</h2>

<h3>PNR13 &#8212; Investment in Fixed Assets (Max 50% of Core Capital)</h3>

<p><b>Regulation:</b> Article 16 &#8212; Fixed assets shall not exceed 50% of core capital</p>

<p><b>Visual 1: Gauge Chart</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Shows the current month sector-wide average ratio</li>
  <li class="compliant">Green zone: 0&#8211;35%</li>
  <li class="warning">Yellow zone: 35&#8211;50%</li>
  <li class="breach">Red zone: 50%+</li>
  <li>One gauge per CATEGORY_TYPE (use small multiples or a slicer)</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Visual 2: Line Chart with Threshold</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>X-axis: Year_Month (rolling 12 months)</li>
  <li>Y-axis: Fixed Assets / Core Capital &#215; 100</li>
  <li>Constant line at 50% (red, dashed)</li>
  <li>One line per institution when filtered, or sector average when unfiltered</li>
  <li>Tooltip: Institution name, absolute amount, ratio</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Why this matters:</b> Fixed asset accumulation can signal capital misallocation. The 50% limit ensures institutions maintain lending capacity.</p>

<hr>

<h3>PNR14 &#8212; Land &amp; Buildings (Max 5% of Total Assets)</h3>

<p><b>Regulation:</b> Article 16 &#8212; Land and buildings shall not exceed 5% of total assets</p>

<p><b>Visual 1: Horizontal Bar Chart with Threshold Line</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Y-axis: Institutions (Stakeholder_Name), sorted by ratio descending</li>
  <li>X-axis: Ratio (%)</li>
  <li>Vertical reference line at 5%</li>
  <li>Conditional bar color: Green &lt; 3%, Yellow 3&#8211;5%, Red &gt; 5%</li>
  <li>Show latest month only</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Visual 2: Heatmap / Matrix with Sparklines</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Rows: Institutions</li>
  <li>Columns: Months (last 12)</li>
  <li>Cell values: Ratio with background color (green/yellow/red)</li>
  <li>Alternative: Use sparklines in cells to show the 12-month trend per institution</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Why this matters:</b> The 5% limit is strict &#8212; even small changes in land valuations can push institutions over the threshold.</p>

<hr>

<h3>PNR15 &#8212; Non-Earning Assets (Max 10% of Total Assets)</h3>

<p><b>Regulation:</b> Article 16 &#8212; Non-earning assets shall not exceed 10% of total assets</p>

<p><b>Visual 1: Traffic Light Table</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Matrix showing each institution&#8217;s ratio per month</li>
  <li>Conditional formatting:</li>
</ul>
<table>
  <tr><th>Range</th><th>Color</th></tr>
  <tr class="compliant"><td>&lt; 7%</td><td>Green</td></tr>
  <tr class="warning"><td>7&#8211;10%</td><td>Amber</td></tr>
  <tr class="breach"><td>&gt; 10%</td><td>Red</td></tr>
</table>
<p>Most practical for supervisors scanning for breaches across many institutions.</p>

<p><b>Visual 2: Stacked Area Chart (Sector Trend)</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>X-axis: Year_Month</li>
  <li>Y-axis: Average Non-Earning Assets Ratio</li>
  <li>Areas stacked by CATEGORY_TYPE (MF, SACCO, OSACCO, DSACCO)</li>
  <li>Threshold line at 10%</li>
  <li>Shows whether non-earning asset ratios are trending up across the sector</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Why this matters:</b> High non-earning assets (foreclosed property, suspended interest, etc.) indicate asset quality deterioration. This norm is an early warning of systemic stress.</p>

<hr>

<h3>PNR16 &#8212; Borrowing Ratio (Max 25% of Total Assets)</h3>

<p><b>Regulation:</b> Article 20 &#8212; External borrowings shall not exceed 25% of total assets</p>

<p><b>Visual 1: Clustered Bar Chart</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Y-axis: Institutions</li>
  <li>X-axis: Borrowing ratio (%)</li>
  <li>Vertical reference line at 25%</li>
  <li>Sorted descending by ratio</li>
  <li>Filter: Latest month</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Visual 2: Waterfall Chart (Monthly Change)</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Shows how the selected institution&#8217;s borrowings changed month-over-month</li>
  <li>Green bars for decreases, red bars for increases</li>
  <li>Useful for institution-level deep dives during inspections</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Why this matters:</b> Over-reliance on external borrowing increases vulnerability to funding disruptions. The 25% cap ensures deposit-funded stability.</p>

<hr>

<h3>PNR17 &#8212; Placement Limits (Max 25% of Core Capital)</h3>

<p><b>Regulation:</b> Article 20 &#8212; Interbank placements shall not exceed 25% of core capital</p>

<p><b>Visual 1: Scatter Plot</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>X-axis: Core Capital (absolute)</li>
  <li>Y-axis: Placements (absolute)</li>
  <li>Diagonal line at 25% (y = 0.25x)</li>
  <li>Points above the line are in breach</li>
  <li>Bubble size: Absolute placement amount</li>
  <li>Color by CATEGORY_TYPE</li>
  <li>Tooltip: Institution name, ratio, amounts</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Visual 2: Line Chart with Threshold</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Same pattern as PNR13 trend chart</li>
  <li>Threshold line at 25%</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Why this matters:</b> Excessive placements with other institutions create concentration and counterparty risk. Monitoring relative to capital ensures proportionality.</p>

<hr>

<h3>PNR18 &#8212; Investment in Equity Shares (Max 25% of Core Capital)</h3>

<p><b>Regulation:</b> Article 20 &#8212; Equity share investments shall not exceed 25% of core capital</p>

<p><b>Visual 1: Ranked Bar Chart</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Institutions ranked by equity investment ratio (descending)</li>
  <li>25% threshold line</li>
  <li>Conditional color: Green &lt; 15%, Yellow 15&#8211;25%, Red &gt; 25%</li>
  <li>Latest month snapshot</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Visual 2: Donut Chart (Composition)</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>For a selected institution, show equity investments as a proportion of core capital</li>
  <li>Inner ring: Core capital breakdown</li>
  <li>Outer ring: Equity investment portion</li>
  <li>Use with a slicer for institution selection</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Why this matters:</b> Equity investments are illiquid and volatile. The 25% cap prevents microfinance institutions from over-concentrating in market risk.</p>

